1 (2) A beverage container, as defined in section 3102, subsection 2, subject to the
2 requirements of chapter 33;
3 (3) A container for architectural paint, as defined in section 2144, subsection 1,
4 paragraph A, as long as a paint stewardship program is in operation, has been
5 approved by the department pursuant to section 2144 and the stewardship
6 organization operating that program:
7 (a) Has demonstrated to the department's satisfaction that it recycles at least
8 90% of the containers of architectural paint collected under the program; or
9 (b) Subject to the approval of the department, if unable to satisfy the
10 requirements of division (a), has demonstrated to the department's satisfaction
11 that it recycles at least 80% of the containers of architectural paint collected
12 under the program; or
13 (4) Excluded from the definition of "packaging material" by the department by
14 rule adopted pursuant to subsection 13, paragraph D.;
15 (5) Used for the containment, protection, delivery, presentation or distribution of
16 drugs, dietary supplements, devices or cosmetics, as those terms are defined in the
17 Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act, infant formula as defined in 21 United
18 States Code, Section 321(z), medical food as defined in 21 United States Code,
19 Section 360ee(b)(3), fortified oral nutritional supplements used by persons who
20 require supplemental or sole source nutrition to meet nutritional needs due to
21 special dietary needs directly related to cancer, chronic kidney disease, diabetes,
22 malnutrition or failure to thrive, as those terms are defined by the World Health
23 Organization's International Classification of Diseases, 11th Revision and
24 biologics and diagnostic kits regulated under the federal Virus-Serum-Toxin Act;
25 (6) Used for the containment, protection, delivery, presentation or distribution of
26 medical equipment or products used in medical settings, including components
27 associated with medical equipment or products used in medical settings and
28 disposable medical equipment; or
29 (7) Used for the containment, protection, delivery, presentation or distribution of
30 products regulated by the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide, and Rodenticide Act.
31 Sec. 3. 38 MRSA §2146, sub-§1, ¶N, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 455, §2, is
32 amended to read:
33 N. "Post-consumer recycled material" means new material produced using material
34 resulting from the recovery, separation, collection and reprocessing of material that
35 would otherwise be disposed of or processed as waste and that was originally intended
36 to be sold for consumption. "Post-consumer recycled material" does not include post-
37 industrial material or pre-consumer material.
38 Sec. 4. 38 MRSA §2146, sub-§1, ¶O, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 455, §2, is repealed
39 and the following enacted in its place:
40 O. "Producer" means:
41 (1) For a product contained, protected, delivered, presented or distributed in or
42 using packaging material and sold or offered for sale at a physical retail location in
43 the State:
Page 2 - 132LR0987(03)
